This Python script takes advantage of Microsoft Windows Virtual Keys codes, using ctypes, in order to automatically control the computer's keyboard and mouse actions.
It includes mapping to both English and Hebrew keyboards.

Information regarding Microsoft Windows codes could be found online:
    Virtual-key codes:
        https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/inputdev/virtual-key-codes
    Mouse events:
        https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winuser/nf-winuser-mouse_event
